2-Ingredient Everything Bagel Chicken Wings
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'wings (wingettes or drumettes)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'everything bagel seasoning'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 390 degrees F (199 degrees C).. Place wings in a large bowl. Sprinkle everything seasoning over the top. Using your hands, mix well until wings are evenly coated.. Place wings in the basket of the air fryer, skin side up. Cook for 20 minutes. Shake and cook until crisp, about 3 minutes more.

name: Miso Chicken Noodle Soup
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '8.5', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'frozen udon noodles'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'rotisserie chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'miso paste'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'everything bagel seasoning,'}
steps: In a saucepan over medium high heat, heat water to boiling. Add udon noodles. Cook until noodles are softened, 4 to 5 minutes.. Add rotisserie chicken. Turn heat to low. Remove 2 to 3 tablespoons water, and stir miso paste into water until smooth. Mix diluted miso paste back into noodles. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes.. Ladle soup into bowls and garnish with everything bagel seasoning.

name: 4-Ingredient Potato Soup
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(28 ounce) bag', 'name': 'potatoes O’Brien with onions and peppers'}, {'quantity': '30', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounce', 'name': 'garlic and herb cheese spread'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'black pepper'}
steps: Place bacon in a large skillet and cook over medium-high heat, turning occasionally, until evenly browned, about 10 minutes. Drain bacon slices on paper towels; chop roughly when cool enough to handle.. Working in batches, pour potatoes into the same skillet, and cook until lightly browned, about 5 minutes. Remove potatoes to a slow cooker. Stir in chicken broth. Dollop cheese spread on top; scatter bacon on top. Cover slow cooker and cook on High until potatoes are very tender, 3 to 4 hours.. If desired, ladle some of the soup, no more than halfway full, into a high powered blender. Cover and hold lid down with a potholder; pulse a few times before leaving on to blend, about 45 seconds.. Pour soup back into slow cooker. Stir to combine; serve immediately.

name: Spinach Artichoke Chicken Bake
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'boneless chicken breast'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'cloves garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fresh basil,'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1 (', 'unit': '14.6 ounce) can', 'name': 'artichoke hearts in water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes,'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'fresh spinach'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'seasoned bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Parmesan cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Heat olive oil and butter together in a large, ovenproof skillet over medium heat.. When butter is sizzling, add chicken pieces. Season with salt and pepper. Brown one side of the chicken pieces, 3 to 5 minutes; turn, and add diced red onion, minced garlic, and minced fresh basil. (See Note.). Cook, stirring often, until garlic is fragrant and onion is softened, about 3 minutes. Season with pepper flakes, and add artichokes and tomatoes. Stir in spinach; remove skillet from heat.. Combine Italian seasoned bread crumbs and shredded Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle bread crumb mixture over skillet contents.. Bake in the center of the preheated oven, uncovered, until bubbly and brown, about 25 minutes. Garnish with fresh basil and serve warm.

name: Apple Cider Cut-Out Cookies
ingredients: {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'apple cider'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'granulated sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground allspice'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'apple cider'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'apple cider'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': "confectioner's sugar"}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'ground cinnamon for sprinkling (optional)'}
steps: Place butter into a light-colored saucepan over medium heat. Cook, stirring frequently, until butter is browned and smells nutty, 5 to 10 minutes. Pour butter into a large mixing bowl.. To the same saucepan, carefully pour in 2 cups of apple cider (it will sputter a bit). Place pan back over medium heat, and cook, stirring often, until cider has reduced to 1/2 cup, 20 to 25 minutes. Measure out 2 tablespoons of the reduced cider; set aside to use for icing. Pour remaining reduced cider into the bowl with browned butter. Allow to cool for 20 minutes.. Add brown sugar, white sugar, egg, vanilla, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg, cloves, and allspice to the butter-cider mixture. Whisk until thoroughly combined. Add in 1 1/2 cups flour, cornstarch, and baking powder, and mix until just combined. Add in remaining 1 1/2 cups flour, and mix until just combined; dough will be thick. Knead dough with your hands a few times until smooth. Pat dough into a flat disc, then wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, or up to 48 hours.. Remove dough from refrigerator. If dough is too stiff to roll out, allow it to sit out at room temperature until it softens slightly, about 15 minutes. Lightly flour a work surface and roll dough out 1/4-inch thick. Cut out cookies using cutters. Gather dough scraps back together, re-roll, and cut out cookies until dough is all used up. Place cut-outs into the refrigerator for at least 15 minutes.. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line cookie sheets with parchment paper. Place chilled cut-outs 1 inch apart on prepared baking sheets.. Bake cookies in the preheated oven, one sheet at a time, until slightly puffed, 10 to 12 minutes. Cool cookies on the pan for several minutes, then remove to a wire rack to cool completely.. For icing, whisk together the reserved 2 tablespoons reduced cider, heavy cream, 1 tablespoons (non-reduced) apple cider, powdered sugar, honey, salt, and vanilla together until smooth. If icing is too thick, add more apple cider until desired consistency is reached; conversely, if icing is too thin, add more powdered sugar to thicken.. Place a wire rack over a baking sheet. Carefully hold a cookie by its edges. Dip the top of the cookie into the icing, then lift straight up to allow excess icing to drip off for several seconds. Carefully invert cookie and place onto the wire rack to catch any icing drips. Lightly sprinkle the top of the cookie with extra cinnamon before icing sets, if desired. Repeat with remaining cookies. Once icing is set, store cookies in an airtight container.

name: Philly Cheesesteak Smothered Tater Tots
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(2 pound)-package', 'name': 'tater tots'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) box', 'name': 'frozen sandwich beef'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Montreal steak seasoning'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Line a large baking sheet with foil; arrange tater tots on the sheet in a single layer.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden, about 20 minutes.. Meanwhile, cook and stir onion, green pepper, and red  pepper in a large skillet over medium-high heat for 5 minutes. Add beef, Worcestershire sauce, and steak seasoning. Cook until most of liquid has evaporated, about 6 minutes.. Divide beef mixture over baked tater tots with a slotted spoon. Sprinkle shredded cheese over the top.. Bake until cheese is melted and beginning to brown, about 5 minutes more.

name: Cottage Cheese Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': '4% milkfat small curd cottage cheese'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'maple syrup'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'quick oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'almond butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'almond flour'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'semisweet chocolate chips'}
steps: Place cottage cheese, maple syrup, oats, almond butter, vanilla, and salt into the cup of a high-speed blender. Blend until ingredients are smooth. Add almond flour to blender and blend until combined. Pulse if necessary to prevent warming the mixture.. Pour dough into a bowl and fold in chocolate chips. Serve immediately, or cover and keep stored in the refrigerator for up to 5 days.

name: Ham and Gruyère Scones
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cooked ham'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Gruyère cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt in a large mixing bowl. Use a pastry cutter to cut butter into flour mixture until it resembles rice or coarse meal. Stir in ham and Gruyère until evenly mixed.. Moisten flour mixture with cream, until dough begins to come together. Add a bit more cream, milk, or water if dough seems dry.. Turn out on a floured work surface and fold dough onto itself. Gently stretch dough, turning and folding 3 or 4 times. Lightly flour a rolling pin and roll dough out 1/2- to 3/4-inch thick, turning dough a quarter turn occasionally.. Cut scones with a lightly floured 3-inch biscuit cutter; press cutter straight down, without twisting. Pat dough scraps together and cut as needed. Line a baking sheet with parchment; place cut scones on the sheet.. Whisk egg, water, and pinch salt together in a small bowl. Brush tops of scones with egg wash, and refrigerate for about 20 minutes.. Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (235 degrees C). Brush the top of the scones with the egg mixture again.. Bake scones in the center of the preheated oven until tops are crispy and lightly browned, 15 to 20 minutes. Serve warm or at room temperature.

name: Honey Glazed Halloumi
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(7 ounce) block', 'name': 'halloumi cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sesame seeds'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili pepper flakes,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': 'fresh', 'name': 'fresh'}
steps: Slice halloumi lengthwise into 6 equal slices and pat dry with a paper towel. Add halloumi slices to a shallow container.. For glaze, combine honey, sesame oil, lime juice, minced garlic, sesame seeds, and chili flakes in a small bowl. Spoon glaze over halloumi, cover, and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour or up to overnight.. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. Place halloumi in the pan, leaving plenty of space between slices. Cook until slices are a nice golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes per side. They will brown quickly.. Lower the heat to a simmer, add any remaining glaze to the skillet to quickly warm up. Spoon glaze over halloumi until well coated.. Place halloumi slices on a plate with some fresh lime wedges, drizzle with any leftover glaze in the skillet, and serve immediately.

name: Pork Tenderloins with Cranberries, Walnuts, and Dried Fruit
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chipotle chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(1 1/2 pound)', 'name': 'pork tenderloins'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'cranberry sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'orange, zested and juiced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried apricots'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried figs'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fresh rosemary'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'rosemary sprigs, for garnish (optional)'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Line a sheet pan with aluminum foil.. Combine ground ginger, light brown sugar, chipotle chili powder, salt, and black pepper in a small bowl; set aside.. Fold about 2 or 3 inches of the thin ends of the tenderloin under the roast and tie 2 times with kitchen string. Oil each tenderloin with 1 tablespoon olive oil. Sprinkle dry seasoning mix evenly on both tenderloins and lightly rub to distribute. Place seasoned tenderloins on the prepared pan.. Roast, uncovered, in the preheated oven until until an instant-read thermometer inserted in the center reaches 135 degrees F (57 degrees C),  20 to 25 minutes.. Remove tenderloins from the oven, tent with foil, and allow to rest about 10 minutes. Internal temperature should rise to a safe 145 degrees F (63 degrees C) during the rest.. Meanwhile, for sauce, melt cranberry sauce in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally. Stir in orange zest, orange juice, and lemon juice. Add apricots, figs, walnuts, and fresh minced rosemary; bring to a boil, then remove from heat, and allow to stand until the tenderloins finish.. To serve, slice tenderloins and place on a serving platter. Add cranberry mixture on top of tenderloin slices, and on the platter. Garnish with fresh rosemary sprigs.

name: Lemon Cranberry Bread
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'buttermilk'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'extra large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh lemon zest'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried cranberries'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'ounce', 'name': 'cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'confectioners sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'fresh lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Generously butter an 8-1/2x4-1/2-inch loaf pan, and line the bottom with parchment paper.. For bread, whisk together sugar, buttermilk, oil, eggs, lemon zest, lemon juice, salt, and vanilla in a large bowl until thoroughly combined. Add in 2 cups flour, baking powder, and baking soda and mix until incorporated.. Toss cranberries with about 1 1/2 teaspoons flour in a small bowl until coated. Fold cranberries into batter. Pour batter into the prepared pan.. Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center of the loaf comes out with just a few moist crumbs, 50 to 60 minutes. Cool bread in the pan for 20 minutes, then remove to a wire rack to cool completely.. For icing, beat cream cheese, confectioner’s sugar, lemon juice, milk, and pinch of salt together in a bowl with an electric mixer until fully smooth and combined. Add more milk if needed for thinner icing, 1/2 teaspoon at a time. Spread glaze evenly over the top of cooled loaf.

name: Air Fryer S’Mores
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'sleeve', 'name': 'graham crackers'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': '(1.5 ounce)', 'name': 'chocolate candy bars'}, {'quantity': '10', 'unit': None, 'name': 's’more-sized marshmallows'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 380 degrees F (193 degrees C). Lay out a total of 10 graham crackers. Do not break apart.. Take 10 s’more size marshmallows and cut them in half horizontally with a serrated knife. Place the sticky side of each marshmallow half onto each square side of a graham cracker rectangle.. Place a piece of parchment into the air fryer basket; place a graham cracker into the basket, marshmallow side facing up. Air fry until marshmallow is toasted, 3 to 4 minutes. Remove carefully.. Gently break marshmallow-topped graham cracker rectangle into 2 squares, add a chocolate bar half on top of 1 square, and sandwich the chocolate with the other square.

name: Cranberry Blush Sparkler
ingredients: {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'ice, as needed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'fluid ounce', 'name': 'vodka'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cranberry sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'fluid ounce', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '1/2 fluid o', 'unit': 'unce', 'name': 'simple syrup'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'fluid ounces', 'name': 'rose champagne, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'cranberries,'}
steps: Fill a cocktail shaker halfway with ice. Add vodka, cranberry sauce, lime juice, and simple syrup. Seal and shake vigorously for 10 to 15 seconds. Strain into a coupe glass or champagne flute, and top with champagne. Garnish with cranberries.

name: 3-Ingredient Potato Soup
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(28 ounce) bag', 'name': "O'Brien hash brown potatoes"}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'bouillon base'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(2.75 ounce) packet', 'name': 'country gravy mix'}
steps: Bring frozen potatoes and water to a boil in a large stock pot. Stir in bouillon base and cook for 15 minutes.. Reduce heat to medium. Whisk in gravy mix. Cook 5 minutes. Turn heat off and let stand until slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.

name: Beet Pickled Deviled Eggs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'beets'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'peppercorns'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'hard boiled eggs'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'Dijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'dash', 'name': 'hot sauce'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'radish slices'}
steps: For brine, drain beet juice into a small saucepan; set beet slices aside. Add the 1/2 cup vinegar, sugar, salt, and peppercorns, and bring to a low boil over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves, 3 to 5 minutes. Let cool completely, about 20 minutes.. Place eggs in a jar or glass bowl just large enough that brine will completely cover eggs; pour in brine. Top up with vinegar as needed to cover eggs completely. Refrigerate, covered, for at least 12 and up to 24 hours. The longer eggs are in brine, the deeper pink they will be.. Slice eggs in half lengthwise from top to bottom with a sharp knife. Remove yolks and place in a bowl. Mash yolks with a fork until smooth, and stir in mayonnaise, Dijon, the 1 teaspoon vinegar, and hot sauce; season with salt and pepper. As an option, if you have a small food processor, place all filling ingredients in it, and blend until smooth.. Spoon filling evenly into egg whites or add mixture to a piping bag or resealable plastic bag with one corner clipped. Pipe mixture into egg white halves, garnish as desired, and serve.

name: Tex-Mex Ground Beef and Potato Skillet
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'hash brown potatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'corn kernels'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'zucchini'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'beef broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes and green chilies, (such as Ro-Tel® Original)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'taco seasoning, mild or hot'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions, sliced'}
steps: Heat a large skillet over medium heat. Cook and stir ground beef, breaking up the pieces as it cooks, until browned and crumbly. 3 to 5 minutes. Drain off excess fat.. Add potatoes, corn, zucchini, beef broth, RO-TEL, taco seasoning, and cumin. Season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat, and simmer until vegetables are tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Taste and adjust seasonings.. Stir in Cheddar, and allow to melt. Remove from heat. Garnish with dollops of sour cream and sliced green onions, and serve immediately.

name: Ploughman’s Sandwich
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bread'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'arugula'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'sweet gherkin pickles'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'smoked ham'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'white Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'tomato'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'mustard'}
steps: Lightly butter both slices of bread.. Layer the arugula, pickles, ham, Cheddar, and tomatoes on one slice of buttered bread. Spread the mustard on the remaining buttered bread slice, and place on top. Cut sandwich in half, and serve.

name: BLT Egg Sliders
ingredients: {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': None, 'name': 'extra large hard boiled eggs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'Roma tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'leaves', 'name': 'Bibb lettuce'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'seasoned salt'}
steps: Place bacon in a large skillet and cook over medium-high heat, turning occasionally, until evenly browned, about 10 minutes. Drain bacon slices on paper towels. Break bacon slices into thirds when cool enough to handle.. Slice eggs in half lengthwise. Place 12 egg halves on a serving plate. Set other egg halves aside.. Spread mayonnaise on 12 egg halves. Top each with 2 pieces of bacon. Top each with 1 tomato slice and 1 folded lettuce leaf.. Top each with a reserved egg half. Secure each "slider" with a toothpick. Sprinkle with seasoned salt and serve.

name: Roasted Red Pepper Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red bell peppers'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lemon, juiced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'cloves garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'ounce', 'name': 'fresh basil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'prepared horseradish'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}
steps: Preheat a grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate. Cut peppers in half. Remove and discard stems, seeds, and membranes.. Place peppers, skin side up, on the preheated grill, directly over heat; cook until slightly charred, 3 to 5 minutes. Turn peppers over and char the other side. Remove from the grill to cool slightly.. Combine peppers, mayonnaise, lemon juice, garlic, horseradish, and smoked paprika in the container of a blender; cover and blend until smooth.

name: Cottage Cheese Brownie Batter
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': '4% milkfat small curd cottage cheese'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'maple syrup,'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsweetened cocoa powder'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'quick oats'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'almond butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'espresso powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'almond flour'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'semisweet chocolate chips'}
steps: Place cottage cheese, maple syrup, cocoa powder, oats, almond butter, vanilla, espresso powder, and salt into the cup of a high-speed blender. Blend until ingredients are smooth. Add almond flour to blender and blend until combined. Pulse if necessary to prevent warming the mixture.. Pour batter into a bowl and fold in chocolate chips. Serve immediately, or cover and keep stored in the refrigerator for up to 5 days.

name: Boursin Chicken, Mushroom, and Asparagus Skillet
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 1/2 to 2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'chicken tenders'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shallots'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'herbes de Provence'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken stock'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white wine'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'asparagus pieces'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(5.2 ounce) package', 'name': 'Boursin® Shallot and Chive Cheese, roughly chopped'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh snipped chives for garnish (optional)'}
steps: Pat chicken tenders dry with paper towels, and season all sides with salt and pepper.. Melt butter with olive oil in a large, nonstick skillet over medium heat. When butter is sizzling, add chicken tenders and cook until browned, 2 to 3 minutes per side. Remove to a plate and keep warm.. Add shallots to the same skillet, and stir for about 30 seconds, then add mushrooms. Stir until mushrooms begin to soften, about 2 minutes. Add garlic and herbes de Provence and cook, stirring, about 30 seconds.. Stir in chicken stock and wine. Add asparagus and another pinch of salt.. Place chicken tenders on top of vegetables, and add any accumulated juices. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and cook until chicken is no longer pink at the center and juices run clear, about 5 minutes. An instant-read thermometer, inserted near the center, should reach 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Turn off heat, add Boursin, and stir until melted. Garnish with chives, if desired, and serve warm.

name: Truffle Deviled Eggs
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'hard-boiled eggs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Dijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'truffle oil'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': '', 'name': 'truffle salt'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chives'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'pieces', 'name': 'truffles (optional)'}
steps: Halve eggs lengthwise and scoop egg yolks into the bowl of a mini food processor; set egg whites aside. If you do not have a mini food processor, you can mash all ingredients in a bowl with a fork.. Add mayonnaise, Dijon mustard, truffle oil, salt, and pepper to the egg yolks; blend well until smooth, scraping down the sides of the bowl. If mixture is too thick, blend in an extra teaspoon or two of mayonnaise.. Place yolk mixture into a resealable bag and snip off a corner. Pipe mixture into egg whites. Top with chives and shaved truffle, and refrigerate until ready to serve.

name: Baked Polenta Marinara
ingredients: {'quantity': '3 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'polenta'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup shredded', 'name': 'mozzarella, divided'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'marinara sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'prosciutto, shredded'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Lightly oil a 9x13-inch baking dish; set aside.. Bring chicken broth to a boil in a saucepan, and whisk in polenta and salt. Immediately reduce temperature to medium, and cook polenta, stirring continuously, until most of the liquid is absorbed and polenta is thick, about 15 minutes. Remove from heat.. Stir Parmesan cheese, 1/4 cup mozzarella, and butter into polenta. Pour mixture into the prepared baking dish and smooth the top.. Bake in the preheated oven until polenta is fairly firm, about 40 minutes. It will firm a bit more on standing.. Remove polenta from the oven; let stand for 5 minutes. Spread marinara over the top, then sprinkle evenly with remaining 1/2 cup mozzarella. Sprinkle top with shredded prosciutto.. Bake polenta until cheese is bubbling and golden brown, about 15 minutes more. Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

name: Bunny Mary
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime wedge'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'celery seed'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'fluid ounces', 'name': 'carrot juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'fluid ounces', 'name': 'vodka'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': 'hot sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'prepared horseradish'}
steps: Place celery seed on a plate. Moisten the rim of a glass with a lime wedge. Dip rim in celery seed until coated. Set aside.. Fill a shaker with ice. Add carrot juice, vodka, lime juice, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, and horseradish. Shake until well combined. Pour into the prepared glass.

name: Creamy Sage and Garlic Pork Chops
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'bone-in', 'name': 'rib pork chops'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'sage'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '15', 'unit': None, 'name': 'sage leaves'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken broth or stock'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white wine'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}
steps: Pat chops dry with paper towels and season both sides with salt, and pepper. Sprinkle both sides of chops with 1 teaspoon rubbed sage, and set aside.. Heat olive oil and butter in a large skillet over medium heat until sizzling. Add sage leaves in a single layer and cook about 2 minutes. Turn and continue cooking until the leaves are crispy, about 2 more minutes. Remove to a paper towel to drain, then chop.. Add seasoned chops to the same skillet and brown both sides, 3 to 5 minutes per side. Remove chops to a plate.. Add minced garlic to the skillet and cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Stir in flour and cook, stirring, until all flour is moistened with the oil and begins to bubble. Add chicken broth and stir rapidly until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes. Pour in white wine and cook, stirring, 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in remaining 1/2 teaspoon rubbed sage.. Gradually stir in cream, and simmer until sauce thickens, about 2 minutes. Return chops to the skillet, and cook in the sauce for an additional 3 to 5 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the center of chops should read 145 degrees F (63 degrees C).. Sprinkle with chopped fried sage leaves and serve immediately.

name: Walking Takis Street Corn
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'ears corn'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(1 ounce) bags', 'name': 'flavored rolled tortilla chips, such as Takis®'}
steps: Heat an outdoor grill over medium-high heat. Grill corn 8 minutes. Flip and grill 8 minutes more. Remove from heat and place on a cutting board.. Whisk mayonnaise, sour cream, Parmesan, cilantro, and black pepper together in a large bowl.. Remove husks from the cob and discard. Cut corn kernels from the cob; stir into mayonnaise mixture.. Open bags of Takis, and divide corn mixture between the bags. Top with extra Parmesan and cilantro if desired. The Takis are your dipping tool. No forks required.

name: Chicken Adobo Tacos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white vinegar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'bay leaves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'granulated garlic'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken thighs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'white vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fish sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'avocado oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'white pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'mango'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'oma tomato'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'jalapeno pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic cloves'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper,'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(8 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}
steps: Combine soy sauce, vinegar, bay leaves, and garlic in a large plastic bag with a zipper. Gently squeeze to mix well. Add chicken and coat with marinade. Squeeze out as much air from the bag as possible, coat all the chicken pieces with marinade, seal, and refrigerate for at least 20 minutes.. Meanwhile, combine vinegar, fish sauce, avocado oil, sugar, and black pepper in a bowl for the salsa. Stir with a whisk or fork until sugar is dissolved. Add mango, tomato, red onion, jalapeño, and chopped cilantro to the bowl. Toss to combine, and refrigerate salsa until ready to serve.. For tacos, remove chicken pieces from the marinade and reserve the marinade.. Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Carefully add the chicken thighs, and brown on each side, 1 to 2 minutes, then remove chicken to a plate.. To the same skillet, add onion, and cook for about 1 minute. Stir in minced garlic and cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add reserved marinade, water, brown sugar, and black pepper, and bring to a boil.. Return chicken to the skillet, smooth side down. Reduce heat to low, and simmer chicken uncovered, about 15 minutes. The liquid should bubble gently. Turn chicken and simmer 10 minutes more. Remove chicken from skillet to rest.. Cook sauce over medium heat until syrupy, thick, and reduced, about 10 minutes. Remove skillet from heat. Remove bay leaves and discard.. Slice chicken into 1/2-inch slices and return to the skillet to coat in the sauce. Garnish with fresh cilantro and chopped green onions, if desired.. Fill each tortilla with chicken strips and top with mango salsa. Serve immediately.

name: Air Fryer Baked Yams
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'yam'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Scrub yam clean and dry with a paper towel. Rub all over with olive oil.. Place yam in the preheated air fryer, and cook until tender when pierced with a fork, 15 to 20 minutes.

name: Peanut Butter Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sweetened condensed milk'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Heat peanut butter and sweetened condensed milk in a saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring until well incorporated and smooth. Stir in milk.. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and salt.

name: Copycat Red Lobster Shrimp Scampi
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'jumbo shrimp (12 to 16 per pound)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'pinot grigio'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'melted butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'freshly squeezed lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'crushed red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'shredded Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'chopped parsley, for garnish'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'lemon wedges, for garnish'}
steps: Gather all ingredients. Preheat the oven’s broiler to 500 degrees F (260 degrees C).. Place shrimp in a pinwheel fashion in an oven-safe dish, such as a glass pie plate.. Stir pinot grigio, melted butter, lemon juice, garlic, salt, and crushed red pepper flakes together in a cup.. Poor mixture over shrimp. Sprinkle Parmesan over shrimp.. Broil until shrimp is pink and tails curl inward, about 7 minutes.. Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve with lemon wedges.

name: One Pot Chicken Pomodoro
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'boneless chicken breasts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic granules'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'shallot'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(28 ounce) can', 'name': 'can crushed tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped fresh basil'}, {'quantity': '1 3/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pinot grigio'}, {'quantity': '16', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'pasta'}
steps: Gather all ingredients. Heat a deep cast iron skillet over medium heat.. Season chicken breasts with salt, garlic, and Italian seasoning.. Pour 2 teaspoons oil into the skillet. Once hot, add chicken. Cook until golden, turning once, about 4 minutes per side. Move chicken to one side of the skillet.. Pour remaining oil into the skillet. Add minced shallot; cook until softened, about 3 minutes. Add the garlic, stir until fragrant, about 1 minute.. Add the crushed tomatoes, salt, sugar, red pepper flakes, and basil. Pour in chicken broth and wine. Stir to combine.. Add pasta to the skillet. Nestle chicken pieces on top of pasta. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover, and cook until pasta is tender with a bite, about 8 minutes. Taste and adjust seasoning; serve immediately.

name: Marry Me Bean Soup
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, pressed'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'great northern beans'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sun-dried tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'tomato sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'spinach'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'basil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Melt butter in a Dutch oven. Add onions and cook until soft and translucent, 5 to 6 minutes.. Add garlic, red pepper, and paprika; cook and stir until garlic is fragrant, about 1 minute.. Add beans, and cook until simmering, about 5 minutes. Mash half of the beans.. Stir in chicken broth, sun-dried tomatoes, and tomato sauce. Add heavy cream and Parmesan cheese, and stir until well combined.. Add spinach and basil and cook until spinach is wilted. Season with salt and pepper.

name: Ramen Omelet with Spinach, Mushrooms, and Cheese
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3 ounce) package', 'name': 'ramen, seasoning packets discarded'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'fresh spinach'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'splash', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cheese'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Bring 2 cups of water to a boil in a saucepan; add ramen and cook until tender, about 3 minutes. Drain and set aside.. Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a skillet. Add mushrooms; cook and stir until tender, about 5 minutes. Add spinach and cook until wilted, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes. Remove from skillet and set aside.. Mix eggs with splash of milk in a bowl. Melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter in the same skillet. Add eggs, top with half of the ramen, 1/2 of the mushroom-spinach mixture, and 1/4 cup cheese. Season with salt and pepper. Once eggs are set, fold omelet in half and top with remaining mushroom mixture and remaining cheese.

name: Mixed Vegetable Curry
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ghee or clarified butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '1/2 inch piece)', 'name': 'ginger,'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'tomato'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'serrano pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'carrots'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green peas'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'russet potato'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground turmeric'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground coriander'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'fenugreek seeds'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped cilantro, for garnish (optional)'}
steps: Heat ghee in a large, nonstick pan over medium heat. Add onion and cook, stirring, until lightly brown, about 8 minutes. Add garlic and ginger and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 1 minute.. Add tomato, serrano pepper, carrots, peas, potato, turmeric, coriander, cumin, fenugreek, chili powder, and salt, and cook, stirring, for about 5 minutes.. Reduce heat to low, cover, and let vegetables steam in their own juices until potatoes are fork tender, about 25 minutes. Stir about halfway through cooking time, and make sure the pan isn't too dry. If vegetables are sticking, add 1 or 2 tablespoons water, replace the lid, and continue cooking. Taste; season with salt.. Garnish with chopped cilantro. Serve warm, with naan, or similar flatbread.

name: Spicy Creamy Cucumber Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'English', 'name': 'cucumbers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'plain Greek yogurt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh lime juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chili sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ketchup'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'hot sauce (such as Tabasco'}
steps: Place sliced cucumbers into a large bowl.. Whisk Greek yogurt, lime juice, Thai chili sauce, ketchup, and hot sauce together in a small bowl until smooth; stir into sliced cucumbers. Refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving.

name: Avocado Caprese Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mozzarella balls, or "pearls," drained'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cherry tomatoes,'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'avocado -'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh basil leaves, or to taste, plus more for garnish (optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'balsamic vinegar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Combine mozzarella, halved cherry tomatoes, and chopped avocado in a small bowl. Tear basil leaves into pieces and sprinkle over the other ingredients.. Drizzle on balsamic vinegar and extra virgin olive oil and toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.. Divide into two serving bowls and garnish with additional fresh basil. Serve immediately.

name: Mississippi Mud Potatoes
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'diced potatoes'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic cloves'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green onions'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Spray an 8x8-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Set aside.. Combine potatoes, cheese, bacon, onion, mayonnaise, garlic, salt, and pepper in a large bowl. Transfer to the prepared dish.. Bake until potatoes are fork tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Top with green onions.

name: Gnocchi Mac and Cheese
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'evaporated milk or half-and-half, or more as needed'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded sharp extra-sharp Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Cheddar cheese powder'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'gnocchi'}
steps: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Melt butter in a saucepan over medium high-heat. Whisk in flour until smooth, and cook about 1 minute.. Whisk in cream, evaporated milk, Worcestershire, and mustard. Stir in Cheddar cheese and cheese powder and cook until cheese melts, about 2 minutes. If you prefer a thinner sauce, add evaporated milk, 1 tablespoon at a time, until sauce is the consistency you like.. Stir in gnocchi; pour mixture into a small baking dish.. Bake in the preheated oven until bubbly, about 20 minutes. Serve immediately.

name: Sheet Pan Summer Gnocchi
ingredients: {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'gnocchi'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'zucchini'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'summer squash'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'onion,'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pint', 'name': 'cherry tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'tomato basil chicken sausage'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic cloves'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'pesto'}
steps: Heat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).. Place gnocchi, zucchini, summer squash, onion, tomatoes, and sausage on a rimmed sheet pan. Drizzle olive oil evenly over mixture. Add garlic and Italian seasoning; toss to coat.. Bake in the preheated oven until vegetables are tender, about 35 minutes. Dollop pesto over the mixture, toss to combine, and serve immediately.

name: Cheesy Zucchini Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'low-sodium chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'long grain rice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded unpeeled zucchini'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cheese'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Bring broth to a boil in a saucepan; stir in rice. Cover, reduce heat to low, and cook until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed, 20 to 25 minutes.. Remove from heat. Stir in melted butter. Add zucchini and cheese. Stir, cover and let sit until cheese is melted, about 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

name: Easy Mozzarella Chicken
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3 pound) package', 'name': 'chicken tenders (such as Just Bare'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(22 ounce) jar', 'name': 'marinara sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'mozzarella cheese slices'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'sliced fresh basil leaves, for garnish'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 360 degrees F (180 degrees C). Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Lightly grease a large casserole dish.. Place frozen chicken pieces in the basket of the air fryer in a single layer. Air fry until golden, about 13 minutes. You may have to work in batches.. Meanwhile, place mozzarella cheese slices between parchment paper and roll thin with a rolling pin; set aside.. Pour half of marinara sauce into the prepared casserole dish.. Place the casserole dish in the preheated oven to warm the sauce, about 5 minutes. Remove from oven; nestle chicken tenders into the sauce. If desired, spread remaining marinara sauce over tenders. Place cheese slices evenly over top of casserole.. Bake until cheese is golden and melted, about 15 minutes. Add cut basil strips to the top for garnish. Serve immediately.

name: Mini Chicken Pot Pies
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 count) packag', 'name': 'frozen mini pie shells'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'pie crust'}, {'quantity': '1 3/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'frozen mixed vegetables'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(5.3-ounce) package', 'name': 'soft French cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1 3/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked chicken'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'water'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a sheet pan with parchment paper, and place individual pie shells on the sheet. Allow refrigerated pie crust to come to room temperature on the counter, about 15 minutes.. Place frozen vegetables into a microwave-safe dish, add water, cover, and microwave on High until hot, about 5 minutes. Drain.. Stir Boursin into vegetables until melted. Stir in cream, chicken, and black pepper; season with salt. Distribute mixture evenly among pie shells.. Using a 3-inch round biscuit cutter, cut 8 circles from refrigerated pie crust. Place a circle on top of each pie and crimp edges together. Using a sharp knife, cut two slits in the form of an "X" in the center of each top crust. Stir egg and water together in a cup until well combined; brush each pie lightly with egg wash.. Bake in the center of the preheated oven until lightly browned, about 20 to 25 minutes, or until lightly browned. Remove to cool on a rack about 10 minutes.. Remove foil tins from pies and serve warm.

name: Corn with Tarragon and Lime
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.4 ounce) package', 'name': 'corn'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter, cubed'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh tarragon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'lime, zested'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Empty frozen corn into a 2-quart saucepan, and stir in water. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, cover, and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 4 minutes. Drain well.. Return saucepan to the stove over low heat, add butter, tarragon, lime zest, and juice. Stir until butter has melted and corn is warm, about 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, and serve.

name: Ramen Vegetable Stir Fry
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'low-sodium soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chili sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'maple syrup'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'ramen noodles (2 packages), flavor packets disgarded'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red pepper'}, {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'broccoli florets'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'sugar snap peas'}
steps: Combine soy sauce, lime juice, Thai chili sauce, maple syrup, ginger, and red pepper flakes in a small bowl. Stir until smooth; set aside.. Bring 4 cups of water to a boil in a pot. Discard flavor packet. Add ramen noodles to boiling water; cook until noodles are tender, 4 to 5 minutes. Drain noodles and set aside.. Heat sesame oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add garlic, onions, red peppers, broccoli, and sugar snap peas, and cook and stir until softened, about 5 minutes. Reduce heat to low; stir in sauce, and cook until thickened, about 3 minutes. Add in ramen noodles and serve warm.

name: Boursin Chicken Baked Ziti
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pecorino Romano cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'breadcrumbs'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ziti pasta'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried Italian herb seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cooked chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh spinach'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(5.2 ounce) package', 'name': 'soft French cheese, such as Boursin® Garlic and Fine Herbs'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C) and grease an 8x8-inch baking dish.. Combine grated pecorino and breadcrumbs in a small bowl; set aside.. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add ziti, and cook until tender with a bite, about 11 minutes. Drain; reserve about 2 tablespoons pasta water.. Meanwhile, melt butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add chopped onion; cook and stir until onion begins to soften, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in garlic, herb seasoning, and red pepper flakes, and cook about 30 seconds.. Turn off heat. Stir in chicken, spinach, cream, Boursin, and mozzarella, stirring until cheeses are melted and ingredients are well combined.. Stir drained ziti into chicken mixture. Loosen the sauce with reserved pasta water, if needed. Pour chicken and sauce mixture into the prepared baking dish. Sprinkle pecorino and bread crumb mixture over the top.. Bake in the center of the preheated oven until bubbly and lightly browned, 20 to 30 minutes. Serve warm.

name: Tuscan Chicken Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'boneless chicken breasts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'talian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'fresh spinach'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(4 ounce) can', 'name': 'sliced mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sun-dried tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, pressed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chicken bouillon granules,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'oil'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Spray an 8x8-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.. Season both sides of chicken with Italian seasoning, paprika, onion powder, pepper flakes, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Place in the prepared pan. Place spinach over chicken, mushrooms over spinach, and sun-dried tomatoes over mushrooms. Top with mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.. For sauce, beat cream, Parmesan cheese, garlic, cream cheese, chicken bouillon, chicken broth, and oil together in a bowl until just combined. Season with salt and pepper. Pour mixture over chicken.. Bake casserole in the preheated oven until bubbly, chicken is no longer pink, and juices run clear, 20 to 25 minutes.  An instant-read thermometer inserted in the center of chicken should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).

name: Sriracha Deviled Eggs with Bacon
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'hard boiled eggs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'plain Greek yogurt'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'sriracha, or to taste, plus more for drizzling'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'yellow mustard'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Cook bacon in a skillet over medium heat until crisp, 4 to 5 minutes, and remove to a paper towel to drain. Chop and set aside.. Slice eggs in half lengthwise, remove yolks, and place in a mini food processor (see Note) Set egg whites aside.. Add mayonnaise, yogurt, sriracha, mustard, vinegar, garlic powder, salt, and pepper to the food processor, and process until smooth.. Spoon filling into egg white halves. Alternately, add mixture to a piping bag or zip-top bag with the corner clipped. Pipe mixture into egg white halves.. Sprinkle deviled eggs with bacon, garnish with a drizzle of sriracha, and serve.

name: Pecan Pie Upside Down Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'nonstick cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light corn syrup'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla paste'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'pecan halves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15.5 ounce) box', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3.5 ounce) package', 'name': 'vanilla pudding'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'oil'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla paste'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spray a 10-inch cake pan with nonstick cooking spray. Line with parchment paper and spray again. Set aside.. Place butter, brown sugar, corn syrup, vanilla paste, cinnamon, and salt in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Add pecans and stir until pecans are coated in mixture. Pour into prepared cake pan and set aside.. For cake batter, place cake mix, eggs, pudding mix, milk, oil, sour cream, and vanilla in a large bowl. Using an electric mixer, beat for 3 minutes. Pour over pecan mixture.. Bake in the preheated oven until a skewer inserted in center comes out clean, 40 to 50 minutes.. Run a butter knife around outside of cake to release from pan. Cool on a wire rack for 10 minutes. Carefully flip cake onto a serving platter and cool completely before slicing.

name: Tuna Melt Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(5.5 ounce) jar', 'name': 'tuna packed in olive oil,'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'rib celery'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '24', 'unit': None, 'name': 'corn tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pickled jalapeno rings'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': None, 'name': 'cherry tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'Monterey Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'sharp Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green onions'}

name: French Almond Rum Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'almond flour'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rum'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'lemon zest'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'almond extract'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'rum'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'confectioners sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced almonds'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Generously grease an 8-inch round cake pan with butter and line the bottom with parchment; then butter the parchment.. For cake, beat butter, brown sugar, white sugar, salt, and nutmeg together in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Add in almond flour, and beat for 1 minute. Add in eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. After last egg has been incorporated, turn mixer speed to medium-high and beat batter for 3 minutes.. Add in 1/4 cup rum, lemon zest, vanilla, and almond extract and mix until combined. Reduce mixer speed to low, add in flour and baking powder and mix until just incorporated. Pour batter into prepared pan and smooth into an even layer.. Bake in the preheated oven until cake is browned and a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes. Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes.. Meanwhile, prepare the syrup. Place water and sugar in a small saucepan over medium-low heat. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sugar is dissolved and mixture is simmering, 2 to 3 minutes. Remove pan from heat and stir in rum. Put pan back over medium-low heat and cook for an additional 2 minutes. Remove pan from heat.. Invert cake onto a wire rack and remove parchment. Leave cake inverted and brush warm syrup over warm cake until all syrup is absorbed. Allow cake to cool completely, about 30 minutes.. For icing, whisk together lemon juice, powdered sugar, pinch of salt, and heavy cream until smooth and combined. If necessary, add extra lemon juice or heavy cream to thin icing to a pourable, but not too thin, consistency.. Place cooled cake onto a serving platter. Pour icing evenly over the cake. Use a spatula or offset knife to smooth over the top if necessary. Sprinkle toasted sliced almonds over icing. Allow icing to set for several minutes before cutting and serving.

name: Shrimp Ramen Stir Fry
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oyster sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'rice vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili crisp,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'grapeseed oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'broccoli florets'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'carrots'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'shrimp'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3 ounce) package', 'name': 'ramen noodles'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'sesame seeds'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions for garnish'}
steps: For sauce, add soy sauce, oyster sauce, sesame oil, rice vinegar, chili crisp, and garlic to a small bowl. Heat grapeseed oil in a small saucepan. Carefully pour heated oil into the bowl; set sauce aside.. Heat remaining 1 teaspoon sesame oil in a wok or heavy skillet. Add broccoli, carrots, bell pepper, and onion. Sauté until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Add garlic and stir until fragrant, about 35 seconds. Pour in sauce, and add shrimp. Cook for approximately 2 minutes.. Meanwhile, open ramen package; discard seasoning packet. Bring 2½ cups water to a boil in a small saucepan. Add noodles and cook for 2 minutes. Drain; stir noodles into the wok; toss to coat. Garnish with black and white sesame seeds, and chopped green onion.

name: Cinnamon Buttermilk Bread
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sugar,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'buttermilk'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'applesauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) and lightly spray a 9x5-inch loaf pan with nonstick spray.. Whisk flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, baking soda, 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon, and salt together in a large bowl. Stir buttermilk, applesauce, eggs, and vanilla together in a cup.. Stir wet ingredients into dry ingredients until well combined. Pour into the prepared loaf pan and smooth the top.. Combine remaining sugar, cinnamon, and butter in a small bowl with a fork until crumbly. Sprinkle over batter in loaf pan.. Bake until a toothpick inserted into the middle comes out clean, about 50 minutes.

name: Quick and Easy No-Chop Chicken and Wild Rice Soup
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'sweet peas and sliced carrots'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'mushroom pieces and stems, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '10 ounce) can', 'name': 'premium chicken breast in water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(4.3 ounce) box', 'name': 'long grain and wild rice mix'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'chopped green onions for garnish (optional)'}
steps: Combine water, broth, peas and carrots, mushrooms, chicken, and rice mix with seasoning in a large pot. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes.. Ladle into bowls; season with salt and pepper. Garnish with chopped green onions.

name: Caramelized Onion Pasta
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'onions'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sun-dried tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chili onion crunch'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'spaghetti'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': '2 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese,'}
steps: Heat olive oil and 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet over medium-low heat. Stir in onions until well coated. Cook, stirring occasionally, until they start to caramelize and turn golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes. You can add water, 1 tablespoon at a time, as onion mixture cooks to speed up caramelization and keep onions moist.. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Stir in sun-dried tomatoes, soy sauce, chili onion crunch, and season with salt and pepper.. Meanwhile, bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook spaghetti in the boiling water, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 12 minutes. Drain, reserving 1/2 cup pasta water.. Transfer pasta to the skillet with caramelized onions. Toss everything together until well coated, and stir in remaining tablespoon of butter. Add reserved pasta water, if needed, a tablespoon at a time.. Garnish with chopped parsley and Parmesan cheese, and serve.

name: Sausage Stuffed Mini Peppers
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'hot Italian sausage'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '5.3-ounce) package', 'name': 'herb flavored Gournay cheese (Such as Boursin'}, {'quantity': '9', 'unit': None, 'name': 'mini bell peppers'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh parsley sprigs or fresh basil for garnish'}
steps: Crumble sausage into a nonstick skillet over medium heat; cook and stir for 2 to 3 minutes.. Add mushrooms, red pepper flakes, and green onions, reserving about 3 tablespoons of green onion tops. Stir until sausage is browned, 3 to 4 more minutes. Drain any excess fat.. Remove skillet from heat and stir in Boursin until melted and well blended with the other ingredients.. Fill each pepper half with about 1 1/2 tablespoons sausage mixture; place filled peppers on a baking sheet.. Preheat the oven’s broiler.. Broil until filling is lightly browned, about 3 minutes. Place on a serving tray and sprinkle with reserved green onion tops. Garnish with sprigs of fresh parsley or fresh basil. Serve warm or at room temperature.

name: Copycat Trader Joe's Gone Bananas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'banana'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'dark chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}
steps: Line a baking sheet with parchment. Slice banana into 1/4-inch thick rounds. Place rounds onto the lined sheet, then place into the freezer. Freeze until solid, about 2 hours.. Place chocolate chips, butter, and oil in a small microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on 50% power for 1 to 2 minutes, stopping to stir every 30 seconds, until chocolate is melted.. Remove banana rounds from freezer. Place one round onto a fork and dip into the chocolate until fully coated. Shake to remove excess chocolate, then use another fork to help slide the chocolate covered banana round back onto the parchment lined baking sheet. Repeat process until all banana pieces are coated in chocolate.. Place chocolate covered banana pieces back into the freezer until chocolate is set, about 30 minutes. Keep stored in the freezer.

name: Apple Pecan and Bacon Salad with Maple Vinaigrette
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'maple syrup'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'apple pie spice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'strips', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red delicious apple'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'ranny Smith apple'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'mixed spring salad greens'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pecans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'ounce', 'name': 'havarti cheese'}
steps: For vinaigrette, add vinegar, maple syrup, olive oil, salt, pepper, and apple pie seasoning to a glass jar with a tight-fitting lid; cover and shake to combine.. Place bacon in a large skillet and cook over medium-high heat, turning occasionally, until evenly browned, about 10 minutes. Drain bacon slices on paper towels.. Combine mixed greens with red delicious apple, Granny Smith apple, and onion in a large bowl. Top with pecans and havarti cheese. Drizzle with vinaigrette and serve immediately.

name: Smoked Pork Chops with Sauerkraut
